There is also a special feature of broadband internet in the establishment. These are the basic facilities and the requirements of every shop-house. The 1 Lorong 16 Geylang fulfills all these requirements.1 Lorong 16 Geylang – AccessibilityThe shop-house is reachable via several MRTs and bus stops. MRTs in the area are Aljunied MRT, Mountbatten MRT, And Dakota MRT. Asia Square Tower 1, located along Marina View at Marina Bay in Singapore, is a twin-tower mixed-use development that will comprise 2 million square feet of grade A office space, a 280-room five-star hotel, 60,000 square feet of retail space and 'The Cube', a 100,000 square foot open public space used for networking or relaxing with a regular programme of exhibitions and performances.

Asia Square Tower 1 feature 43 floors with the hotel occupying the 32nd to 46th floors. The retail space within Asia Square Tower 1 will be located on the 1st and 2nd floors in both towers.

The development will enjoy direct frontage onto the Central Linear Park, a public open park linking Marina Boulevard to Straits Boulevard.

Asia Square Tower 1 is located in close proximity to two existing MRT stations (Raffles Place and Marina Bay) and will be linked underground to the future Downtown MRT Station along the Downtown Line.

Asia Square Tower 2, located along Marina View at Marina Bay in Singapore, is a twin-tower mixed-use development that will comprise 2 million square feet of grade A office space, a 280-room five-star hotel, 60,000 square feet of retail space and 'The Cube', a 100,000 square foot open public space used for networking or relaxing with a regular programme of exhibitions and performances.

The development is currently under construction and will be completed in 2013.

Asia Square Tower 2 will feature 46 floors with the hotel occupying the 32nd to 46th floors. The retail space within Asia Square Tower 2 will be located on the 1st and 2nd floors.

The development will enjoy direct frontage onto the Central Linear Park, a public open park linking Marina Boulevard to Straits Boulevard.

Asia Square Tower 2 is located in close proximity to two existing MRT stations (Raffles Place and Marina Bay) and will be linked underground to the future Downtown MRT Station along the Downtown Line.

In terms of accessibility, it is approx. 0.7 km away from NS2 Bukit Batok MRT Station and is surrounded by a high mix of retail, amenities and food & beverage at Bukit Batok Central and West Mall.

Target to obtain TOP in the first quarter of 2017, Carros Centre is set to be the largest freehold automobile mega hub in Singapore. The industrial integrated development is located at 60 Jalan Lam Huat within Sungei Kadut. The 8-storey building comprises of 383 strata units including two food and beverage outlets in total and sprawling over 2.3 million square feet of freehold floor space. 

The development will house automobile-related facilities such as car service centres, automobile repair service facilities, body works and servicing workshops, parts and supplies dealerships and storage for new and pre-owned car dealerships. Each floor can easily house over 1,600 vehicles. Carros Centre is developed by BS Capital Group, a property developer with a diversified portfolio of industrial, commercial, retail and residential assets. Ramp up access is available for all units. There are four 40-ft container loading and unloading bays at Level 1. The strata unit sizes range from 154 sqm to more than 1,000 sqm. Business owners can choose to combine their space with adjoining units, if required.

Carros Centre is easily accessible via major expressways in Singapore. Drivers will find it easy to get to Carros Centre as it is well connected to the Bukit Timah Expressway, Seletar Expressway and Kranji Expressway. It will also be easy for train commuters to travel to Carros Centre. It is in close proximity to the MRT North South line and the future MRT line towards Johor Bahru.

Claymore Connect is within a short walking distance of Orchard MRT station, situated at the junction of Scotts Road, Paterson Road and Orchard Road. Its main entrance is along Claymore Road, with direct access to Orchard Hotel from the mall's mezzanine floor and Level 2. The redeveloped mall received its TOP in March 2015 and was officially opened on 8 October 2015.

Joining the ranks of family-oriented malls on Orchard Road, the newly refurbished mall with enhanced retail offerings caters to the growing captive residential population in the nearby precincts of Tanglin, Orchard and Claymore, given the increasing number of residential developments in these areas. Orchard Hotel guests are able to enjoy the convenience of the F&B outlets, beauty, wellness and lifestyle services at the mall.

The mall also offers a diverse range of food and beverage selections, and a number of lifestyle and fashion retailers. Claymore Connect also features a number of beauty and wellness outlets ready to pamper discerning patrons.

column7: Ophir-Rochor Residential Pte Ltd (Malaysia Khazanah and Singapore Temasek Holdings)
column13:
DUO Galleria is a 39-storey commercial building offering an approximate net lettable area of 570,000 square feet premium Grade A office over twenty levels. With an approximate net floor plate of up to 31,000 square feet, DUO Galleria offers the largest floor-plate in the Bugis district micro-market.  

A 352-room five-star hotel occupies levels 25 to 37 of DUO Galleria, with a signature restaurant on level 38, observation deck on level 39 and amenities including ballrooms, meeting rooms, all-day dining restaurant, outdoor swimming pool, pool bar, executive lounge, fitness centre, spa wellness area.

DUO Galleria is part of an integrated mixed-use development located at Ophir-Rochor and scheduled for completion in 2017.

It is close to the financial and business districts of Marina Bay and Raffles Place, yet outside the Central Business District (CBD) Electronic Road Pricing (ERP) Gantry.  Changi Airport is a mere 15-minute drive via East Coast Parkway (ECP).

DUO Galleria is directly connected to the Bugis MRT Station (EW12) along the East-West Line and Downtown Line (DT14) via Underground Pedestrian Network (UPN), providing access to the Central Business District, major shopping, dining and entertainment areas at Orchard Road and the Singapore River. 

Flanked by the bustling arts, cultural, entertainment and education hub at Bras Basah- Bugis area and the conserved historic districts of Kampong Glam and Beach Road, DUO Galleria corridor is set amidst a hive of activities within 5-minute walk to major shopping malls like Bugis Junction and Bugis+, with sidewalk cafes and alfresco eateries at nearby Haji Lane and Arab Street.

Golden Mile ComplexGolden Mile Complex is high-rise mixed development built on a 99-year leasehold land situated on Beach Road, Singapore. The developer of this property is Singapura Developments, a Singapore based real estate company which was founded in 1963. Built on a 1.3-hectares piece of leasehold land and towering up to a 16-storey height, the building was previously called Woh Hup Complex. The completion of its development took place in 1974. It hosts shop lots, commercial spaces as well as the apartment units; a total of 411 shops, 68 residential units and 226 offices. It is located near Nicoll Highway MRT Station, Arab Street as well as Raffles Hospital, among other public amenities. The project is easily accessible through Nicoll Highway MRT Station, Lavender MRT Stations or BUGIS MRT Station, all located very near to the project. Nicoll Highway links the development to the Orchard Road business hub while Central Expressway connects it to the Orchard Road shopping district. Traveling to either of the destinations from the property needs just a ten-minute drive. It hosts various amenities such as clubs, shops, food stalls, and offices like ticketing agencies for travelers.Golden Mile Complex - Unique Selling PointsSituated in the heart of Singapore, Golden Mile Complex is a cool place to be lived by tourists as well as the locals. Moving to and fro the property isn’t a hassle since it is well connected to various established areas through railway stations and major highways. Besides, the development is a prominent departure or drop-off spot, with various popular bus companies selling their tickets on its ground floor. An apartment in this project is a place where nearly everyone would like to call a home, courtesy of the conveniences. Designed by three prominent DP Architects designers, Gan Oon, William Lim and Tay Kheng, the complex is an outstanding landmark in Singapore. Its unique design attracts many design enthusiasts and scholars. In 2007, National University of Singapore’s students visited the building during Singapore Architectural Festival to learn more about the unique features of the design. The design, among other functions, reduces the impact of noise resulting from the road traffic and enhances the penetration of the natural light into the building. People who live in the property’s apartment find shopping to be a breeze since there are lots of shops at the lower levels of the tower. The access to education shouldn’t be a problem to the residents as the vicinity of the property has numerous learning centres like Farrer Park Primary School, Jewellery Design & Management International School, Insworld Institute, Stamford Primary School, and Bendemeer Primary School. Those residing in the apartments on the upper floor have an added advantage of viewing the beautiful sea and the sky without obstruction.Golden Mile Complex – AccessibilityGolden Mile Complex can be easily accessed through Nicoll Highway MRT Station, Lavender MRT Stations or BUGIS MRT Station; all located very near to the project. A drive of ten minutes from the property through Nicoll Highway will take you to the locality’s business hub while the same distance through Central Expressway is enough to reach the Orchard Road shopping district. There are numerous educations centers within a radius of 2.76 km from the property and they include Nanyang Academy of Fine Arts, Jewellery Design & Management International School, Singapore Management University, St Joseph Institutional International, Laselle College of the Arts, Farrer Park Primary School, Bendemeer Primary School and Stamford Primary School. The project is also located near shopping venues such as Suntec City Shopping Mall, Shaw Centre Shopping Mall and Bugis Junction Shopping Mall. Other amenities found in the neighborhood of the property include restaurants, banks, recreation venues, cinemas and boutique shops.Golden Mile Complex - Amenities & AttractionsShopping near Golden Mile Complex:Suntec City Shopping MallShaw Centre Shopping MallBugis Junction Shopping MallSchools and Education near Golden Mile Complex:Nanyang Academy of Fine ArtsJewellery Design & Management International SchoolSingapore Management UniversitySt Joseph Institutional InternationalLaselle College of the ArtsFarrer Park Primary SchoolBendemeer Primary SchoolStamford Primary SchoolInsworld InstituteGolden Mile Complex - Project informationGold Mile Complex is built on a 1.3-hectares piece of 99-years leasehold land. It has a total of 16 storeys hosting a sum of 411 shops, 68 apartment units and 226 offices. There are two-storey penthouses among the residential units. Each apartment comes with a balcony where the residents can enjoy the beautiful view of the sea as well as the sky.The amenities hosted by the complex include retail shops, offices and a whopping 500 car parking spaces.Project Name: Golden Mile ComplexDistrict: 7Configuration:411 shops68 residential units226 officesGolden Mile Complex - Nearby ProjectsThe following developments are in the same neighbourhood as Golden Mile Complex:Golden Beach Vista HDB FlatsSultan Plaza.

column7: Orchard Turn Developments (Capitaland and Sun Hung Kai Property)
column13: ION OrchardION Orchard, previously called Orchard Turn Site, is a premier mall located at Orchard Road in Singapore. The developer of this project is Orchard Turn Developments Pte Ltd, a property development company formed as a result of a joint venture by CapitaLand Limited together with Sun Hung Kai Properties. Capital Land Limited is a real estate firm based in Singapore. The company was incorporated in the year 2000 when DBS Land and Pidemco Land companies merged. With the largest fund management businesses in Asia’s real estate industry, the company is one of the biggest real estate firms in the entire continent. On the other hand, Sun Hung Kai Properties is a prominent property development company based in Hong Kong. The investment holding company is a property investor besides developing high-quality properties for sale and rent. Completed in 2009, this iconic development, ION Orchard, comprises 355 retail and F&B outlets featuring state-of-the-art design. The mall is a component of The Orchard Residences, a high-rise condominium with 56 storeys. Built on a leasehold land with a tenure of 99 years, the building is the tallest tower in Orchard Road. The property can be accessed through bus services offered by SBS Transit, SMRT Buses as well as Tower Transit Singapore. Alternatively, people who prefer private transport to public transport can use Orchard Boulevard to reach the development. The property hosts facilities like a sophisticated canvas media wall using several senses, club facilities and an observation deck.ION Orchard - Unique Selling PointsION Orchard is the ultimate place to shop, dine, have fun or invest for high returns. Equipped with state-of-the-art facilities and design, the mall is one of the lucrative properties where many savvy investors eye to own at least something. Tenants are always ready to occupy any vacant outlet in the property, hence consistently high monthly rental returns is something that the owners of this property don’t worry about. Do you want to know why the property is such a hot cake? Well, to start with, it experiences insanely high traffic of art lovers who visit here frequently to have a look at the best Asian and Singaporean modern art and design displayed in the mall. The property also hosts local as well as international exhibitions that are rare to find elsewhere, particularly in Singapore. Additionally, the mall offers an unrivaled shopping experience, thanks to the presence of top world-class, luxury brands establishing themselves in the duplex units facing Orchard road. The visitors have a privilege of enjoying an assortment of dishes, be it local delicacies or international cuisines, from a vast food mall located within the property. As a result, the mall won two awards during the PeopIe’s Choice Award function held in 2016; the first being the Best Luxury Shopping Centre while the second was the Best Shopping Centre. The mall is indeed a must-invest property.ION Orchard – AccessibilityION Orchard can be accessed through bus services offered by SBS Transit, SMRT Buses as well as Tower Transit Singapore. Additionally, the property can be reached through trains which serve at Orchard MRT Station. Alternatively, people who prefer private transport to public transport can use Orchard Boulevard. Besides Orchard MRT Station, other nearby train stations are Somerset MRT Station and Newton MRT Station, being only 0.82 kilometers and 1.16 kilometers away, respectively. Schools located near the mall include International School Singapore, International Schools Singapore and Overseas Family School.ION Orchard - Amenities & AttractionsSchools and Education near ION Orchard:International School SingaporeInternational Schools SingaporeOverseas Family School.ION Orchard - Project informationThe ION Orchard is equipped with various modern facilities like a sophisticated canvas media wall (Media Façade) which supports state-of-the-art technology with several senses. The mall will also provide a very large public square where people can meet to share ideas. There’s a gallery known as ION Art where top-notch art and design display as well the best local and world-class exhibitions take place. Besides, the shopping mall hosts an observation deck known as ION Sky in its 55th as well as the 56th floor. From this deck, a viewer will enjoy the city’s unobstructed view. The mall also has a garden on the ninth floor and club facilities on the same floor as well as the 30th floor. From fourth to the eight floors of the mall, there is a large car park hosting roughly 650 lots.Project Name: ION OrchardDistrict: 9Configuration: 355 residential unitsION Orchard - Related ProjectsThe following projects are by the same developer as ION Orchard:Junction 8DeauvilleOcean WingsPark YohoION Orchard - Nearby ProjectsThe following developments are in the same neighbourhood as ION Orchard:Orchard Ville Oxley MansionCavenagh Mansions.

ParkSuitesParkSuites is a private low-rise apartment/retail condominium located at 18-32 Holland Grove Road in District 10. The project was developed by Kentish View Pte Ltd and Lucky Pinnacle Pte Ltd under the umbrella of Far East Organization real estate company. The condo was designed to give a homely feel to people of different age, gender, ethnicity, and marital status. The neighbourhood of ParkSuites is very welcoming, and also offer access to various amenities and recreational activities.Unique Selling PointsParkSuites is fashioned after very modern designs and features most indoor facilities residents would ever dream of having in their condominium building. A 50-metre lap pool, Kids' pool, reflecting pool, recreational pool, Garden terrace, sun deck, and jacuzzi are all options within the building for relaxation. ParkSuites also has a Gym for fitness, BBQ pavilion, Party deck, and Dining pavilion for small parties.AccessibilityAdults and children have access to different routes for commuting to their various destinations from ParkSuites. Dover MRT station is the nearest route to the condo and is often considered the best transport option for people living in the apartment. Holland Village MRT station, Commonwealth MRT station, and Buona Vista MRT station are also available transport routes from the condo to destinations in nearby cities. Alternative routes with easy access are available for private car owners through Aye Rajah (AYE) Expressway from ParkSuites condo.Amenities & AttractionsParkSuites condo is a short distance away from amenities which will satisfy all needs and desires of residents. Several restaurants, take-out food joints, pastry houses, and food retailers are around ParkSuites to keep residents well fed at all times.Education centresPrestigious educational facilities likeHenry Park Primary SchoolGhim Moh Primary SchoolNexus International SchoolAnglo Chinese Junior CollegeFairfield Methodist School (Primary)Eunoia Junior CollegeTertiary institutes are not far off either,the Singapore Polytechnicthe National University of SingaporeShopping near Placename:Coronation Shopping PlazaHolland Road Shopping CentreThe Star VistaAnchor Point Shopping CentreJelita Shopping Center,Bukit Timah PlazaOther Shopping VenuesSports Recreation Temasik Club Driving RangeSixth AvenueSaddle ClubHolland VillageChip Bee GardensRochester ParkSingapore Island Country ClubBukit Timah Nature ReserveKing Albert parkProject InformationParkSuites is a low-rise private five-tower apartment /retail condo with five blocks and a minimum of four storeys per block. The project which has a 110-year leasehold tenure on a site area of 9,402 sq m (101,203 sq ft) housing a total of 119 Residential units and 18 Retail units. The available units have different unique apartment specification from 1 bedroom to four bedrooms.Project Name: PlacenameDistrict: 10Configuration: 119 Residential units and 18 Retail unitsThe available unit types in ParkSuites are;1 Bedroom (441- 452 sq ft)1 Bedroom + Study ( 452 sq ft)2 Bedroom (646 - 893 sq ft)2 Bedroom + Study (840 - 850 sq ft)2 Bedroom Dual-Key3 Bedroom Dual-Key (797 - 1163 sq ft)4 Bedroom Triplex (1281 – 1647 sq ft)The proposed average selling price for residential units will start from S$1, 300 for units with one bedroom, and S$ 1,900 for units with two bedrooms.Far East Organisation under the accounts of Kentish View Pte Ltd and Lucky Pinnacle Pte Ltd were responsible for ParkSuite development project. The developer is well known all over Singapore for reputable and quality real estate constructions in both private and public sectors. So far, the company has been responsible for 45,500 private homes in Singapore and are considered the key contributors to urbanization in Singapore. Some of their notable residential works include; Holland Grove, The Clift, The Altez, The Seahill, The Scotts Tower, Greenwood Mews, Urban Resort, Orchard Scotts, Cyan, The Lanai, The Seaweed, Boulevard Hue, and EuHabitat.Nearby ProjectsParkSuites has a serene and beautiful ambience and gives residents a charming feel when they take a walk around the exterior of the condo. The contributing factor to the ambience is the presence of nearby apartments like :Evian CondominiumVentura HeightsQueen Astrid GardensZion MansionLink Residence @ HollandDynasty Garden Court 2.

Roxy SquareRoxy Square is an old but beautiful mixed development located at 50 East Coast Road, Singapore. It contains both residential apartment units and a shopping center with commercial units below. This project was completed by the famous Fraser Centerpoint Group, which is a very well reputed group in the field of construction. It is a great development and is considered to be one of the main centers of the city.Roxy Square - Unique Selling PointsRoxy Square does not provide its residents with the modern facilities like the residents of many new developments have but it provides its residents with full condo facilities to make sure that they enjoy their time in the development.Roxy square provides complete car parking facility not just for residents of the development, but also for the consumers who come to shop from the shopping center of the Roxy Square. Most importantly, the development is equipped with modern security gadgets and provides 24 hour security to the residents and consumers of the Roxy Square development safe for the residents and the consumers both.Roxy Square – AccessibilityRoxy Square is indeed a great place to live in. It is surrounded by beautiful developments and a variety of amenities. The residents of the development do not have to worry about anything because everything is easily available in the area. There are many famous educational institutions in the area providing top class education services to the people of the area. Few of the famous educational institutions near the development are namely Sam Kian School, Tanjong Katong Primary School and Chatsworth International School. It is considered to be a great place for those who love to do shopping because there are many famous shopping spots in the area. Few of the famous shopping areas near the development are namely 112 Katong Mall, BearBitInc and the shopping mall of the Roxy Square itself from where the residents can shop for almost anything they want. There are many hospitals and medical clinics as well in the area providing top class medical services where the residents can go in case of any medical situation. Few of the famous medical clinics and hospitals near the development are namely International Medical Clinic – Katong, Annie Tiang TCM (AT TCM) and TCMTrend Clinic. Roxy Square was developed strategically keeping in mind the importance of accessibility of the location. The residents do not have to worry about moving to and from the location. Public transportation is also available in the locality making the development even more attractive. The residents can use EW7 Eunos MRT Station, CC8 Dakota MRT station and EW8 Paya Lebar MRT Station to move to and from the location if they do not have their own vehicle. The development is easily accessible and is connected via major roads and highways of the area from where the residents can go to any place of the city just by driving a few minutes.Roxy Square - Amenities & AttractionsSchools and Education near Roxy Square:Sam Kian SchoolTanjong Katong Primary SchoolChatsworth International SchoolShopping near Roxy Square:112 Katong MallBearBitIncMedical Centres/Clinics near Roxy Square :Medical Clinic – KatongAnnie Tiang TCM (AT TCM)TCMTrend ClinicRoxy Square - Project informationRoxy Square is a beautiful development. The owners have the option to select from residential and commercial units. The residential apartments of the development comprises of a single bedroom with a built up area of 603 sf. The design of the units in the development is cutting edge and units provide complete privacy to its residents. The units in the development are beautiful and spacious and are developed in such a way that the residents can enjoy the nature lighting and feel the natural environment. The owners also have the option to rent out the unit, making the development attractive from investment point of view as well.As discussed earlier, the construction of this development was done by the famous Fraser Centerpoint Group, which is a very well reputed group in the field of construction. They have developed many famous projects in the country and they focus on giving value back to their stakeholders. They made sure that there was no cost cutting done on the project and everything in the development was of international standards. The developers made sure that the Roxy Square development not only attracts people who just want to live in it, but also attracts people who want to invest in it because investors can straight away start getting the return on their investment by renting out the units.Project Name: Roxy SquareDistrict: 15Configuration: 88 residential unitsUnit types for Roxy Square :Single bedroom (603 sf)Roxy Square - Nearby ProjectsThe following developments are in the same neighbourhood as Roxy Square:Marine BlueModa.
